[SN]TITLE[SN]
Gay Christians 'feel betrayed' by Church's stance on sexuality

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Gay and lesbian Christians who were consulted by the Church feel "betrayed" by its stance on sexuality, the former bishop of Worcester has said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
11 February 2017 Last updated at 23:34 GMT
The Rt Rev Peter Selby is one of 14 retired bishops who have criticised the Church's position on sexuality, days before a crucial debate at the governing general synod.
Last month, a report recommended the Church's opposition to same-sex marriage should not be changed.
